FBIS4-15310 "drsov068_i_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-068 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Kazakhstan Nazarbayev Backs Japan's Permanent UNSC Membership Bid Nazarbayev Backs Japan's Permanent UNSC Membership Bid LD0704153994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1256 GMT 7 Apr 94 LD0704153994 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by KAZTAG correspondent for TASS] [Text] Tokyo 7 April, TASS -- Kazakhstan supported the Japanese wish to become a permanent member of the UN Security Council and the two countries pledged to promote their political dialogue on international and regional issues, according to a joint statement signed on Thursday by Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev and Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa. Japan agreed to grant a 220-million dollar credit to Kazakhstan which pledged to continue market reforms, attract foreign investments and improve economic legislation. Japan also welcomed that Kazakstan, one of the four former Soviet nuclear republics, had joined the nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty as a nuclear-free state. The parties agreed to cooperate in accelerating the solution of issues connected with the elimination of nuclear weapons in Kazakhstan.
